      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TINNY MAHONEY (1) has won two of his last three starts at Tamworth, leading from this barrier both times. Owns a decent record at this distance and could be hard to catch again. Hard to knock the recent consistency of DONNIE MAC (4) who added to a string of top-two finishes when he raced three wide without cover but scored by 4.6m at Wagga last week. Similar draw and could strike again. SINBAD SASSY (6) was first up for six months when runner-up to DONNIE MAC at Wagga. Has won when second-up before so should be improved. There wasn't much between JEWEL HEAVEN (3) and BEANCOUNTER (2) when finishing one-two in their heat at Bathurst and both draw to be competitive.",
